<br>
Reagents.  I know that 50+ reagents for pets are comparatively cheap for necros and mages, but beastlords do not need them to summon our pet.  Thus if the beastlord pet dies its an even smaller loss.  Not to mention the more mana efficent heals.  The beastlord pet tanking seems to me the best choice.<br>
<br>
Spirit of the Storm:  This is a proc beastlords can put on their pets beggining at level 53.  When it goes off it not only deals damage but acts adds a substantial amount of taunt power (200) as well.  Thus should a healer or nuker generate too much aggro a beastlords pet with this proc can get the mob off of the player usually in just one proc.  It also helps raise the overall pet taunt of the pets.  As has been mentioned by fellow beastlords all pets on a given mob share a collective taunt that allows them to take the punishment from melee's.  Storm just makes it even easier for a melee to get in and not get hurt.<br>
<br>
Other than that, I want to agree that pet groups are awesome.  I had one with 2 beastlords 2 mages and 2 necros.  Was the BEST experience group I've ever had.  What really helped was the epic necro.  6 pets and 2 beastlords beating on a mob with 2 mages nuking, we were ripping them to shreds 2 at a time.<br>
